<doc>
  <member name="eAVDSPLoudnessEqualization">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies whether loudness equalization is enabled in an audio decoder or digital signal processor (DSP). This enumeration is used with the <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/DirectShow/avdsploudnessequalization-property">AVDSPLoudnessEqualization</a> property.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>Loudness equalization is a DSP process that maintains a consistent volume level when the audio stream changes.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/DirectShow/codec-api-enumerations">Codec API Enumerations</seealso>
    <seealso cref="ICodecAPI Interface" />
  </member>
  <member name="eAVDSPLoudnessEqualization.eAVDSPLoudnessEqualization_OFF">
    <summary>
      <para>Loudness equalization is disabled.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="eAVDSPLoudnessEqualization.eAVDSPLoudnessEqualization_ON">
    <summary>
      <para>Loudness equalization is enabled.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="eAVDSPLoudnessEqualization.eAVDSPLoudnessEqualization_AUTO">
    <summary>
      <para>The decoder or DSP automatically selects the equalization mode.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>